This is... "the power to protect people"... It's strong,
isn't it...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]Of course. You, Amy-chan, are among those I must protect. I
can't afford to lose.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]I might not fully understand your sadness or pain, Amy-chan.
But I can be there for you from now on.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[0]Besides, if you ever need to vent your painful feelings,
I'll be here to listen anytime!

That's just because you want to fight, isn't it, big
sister...

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Ahaha, you caught me♪ It's just that you were so strong,
Amy-chan, I couldn't help but want to battle again.
Big sister, you really are "free," aren't you.

The rules set by the Guardians aren't meant to bind our
freedom... I think I'm starting to understand that.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]That's right. A battle without rules wouldn't be fun or
interesting at all!

Hehe, it feels like we're not quite on the same page, but
that's just like you, big sister.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[8]I feel like I'm being made fun of, but since
\FaceIndex[1]Amy-chan is smiling, I guess it's okay♪

Big sister, beyond this door is the anti-Guardian weapon
that Liberator [Belial] has prepared. If it gets activated,
it will probably cause a lot of trouble.
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[11]We have to stop it at all costs!!

I'll go and try to stop Belial from activating the weapon.
In the meantime, big sister, you go and deactivate the
barrier again. Then we'll be able to communicate with the
outside again.

\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[2]Eh... But I've always left that kind of thing to Hisana-
chan, so I don't know how to deactivate it?

It's okay. The barrier will stop if you destroy the terminal
on the \c[2]rooftop\c[0].
\PartyFace[1]\FaceIndex[1]Oh, that's a relief. It's such a simple thing.
